      <p>Hi Molly,</>I bought a decadently large bunch of basil at the market yesterdat so I could make this. It&#8217;s been outrageously hot here, and this lemonade is perfect!</></>And please don&#8217;t fret about how much focus your wedding needs. I purposefully got married out of the country to avoid having a big &#8220;American wedding&#8221; and turning into a typical &#8220;American bride.&#8221; But you know what? No matter where you are, a wedding is an intensely personal event that&#8217;s celebrated in public. That alone lends tremendous stress and additional work to the occasion &#8211; never mind that it&#8217;s the biggest party most of us will ever throw for ourselves (rather than for someone else). You are so far from being the narcissistic type that turns into a bridezilla, and I&#8217;m sure you know that. So it&#8217;s fine to be as focused as you are on the wedding, is what I&#8217;m trying to say. Just try to enjoy it whenever you can, and know that everyone is very, very happy for you.</p>
