    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Your wedding <>is<> a party, one of the biggest you&#8217;ll ever throw (not necessarily just because of the guest list but because it is, you know, a rather important day).  So of course there are details and bits that make you go &#8220;blaaaagh!&#8221;.  But as a wise priest once told me, &#8220;If you show up and he shows up and I show up, then by the end of the day, you&#8217;ll be married&#8221;.  That&#8217;s all it takes, the rest is just for fun.  Do try to have fun with it and promise yourself to be present at your own wedding.  (You don&#8217;t know how many women I know who have virtually no recollection of the day because they were so obsessed with details).  Have fun, love him and enjoy yourself.  That&#8217;s a pretty good recipe for a successful marriage, too!</p>
