  <li id="comment-8082" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/01493708300940204826" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Molly</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2007/07/my-lemonade-fix/#comment-8082"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2007-07-20T05:43:00-04:00">Friday, July 20, 2007 at 5:43 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>No problem, Julie!  By &#8220;strips of lemon zest,&#8221; yes, I do mean thin strips of lemon rind.  I shave them off with a paring knife, taking just the yellow rind and not the white pith.  Hope you enjoy it&#8230;</p>
